ames © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the three places called Harrington (Cumberland, Lincolnshire, Northamptonshire). The Cumberland placename derives from the Old English personal name <i>Hæfer</i> + Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. The Lincolnshire placename derives from the Old English personal name <i>Hearra</i> + Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>tūn</i>. The Northamptonshire derives from an Old English personal name <i>Hǣthhere</i> + Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’. Compare   Herendeen  .","Irish: adopted as an Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hArrachtáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Arrachtán</i>’, a personal name from a diminutive of <i>arrachtach</i> ‘mighty, powerful’.","Irish: in Kerry, this name was adopted as an Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hIongardail</b>, later <b>Ó hUrdáil</b>, ‘descendant of <i>Iongardal</i>’, a personal name of uncertain origin."],"variants":[{"name":"Herington","meanings":["English: variant of   Harrington   or   Herrington  ."]},{"name":"Herrington","meanings":["English:","habitational name from Heronden in Tenterden (Kent) or Herrington in Houghton (Durham). The Kent placename may derive from an Old English personal name <i>Hȳra</i> + Old English connective <i>-ing-</i> + <i>denn</i> ‘pasture’, while the Durham placename may come from Old English <i>hæring</i> ‘rocky place’ (from <i>hær</i> ‘rock, heap of stones’ + the placename forming suffix <i>-ing</i>) or <i>hæren</i> ‘rocky’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’.","variant of   Harrington  ."]},{"name":"Herendeen","meanings":["Altered form of English   Harrington  ."]},{"name":"Arrington","meanings":["English:","variant of   Harrington   with loss of initial <i>H-</i>.","possibly a habitational name from Arrington, a place in Cambridgeshire, named from an Old English byname, <i>Earn(a)</i>, meaning ‘eagle’ + <i>-inga-</i> ‘people or followers of’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘settlement’."]}]},{"name":"Catherine","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."],"variants":[{"name":"Catheryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Katherine","meanings":["equivalent of   Katherine  , also occasionally used in the English-speaking world."]},{"name":"Catharin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathryn","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Cathrin","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]},{"name":"Catharine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Catherine Harrington was born in 1386, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 6 sons with Robert Caldwell. She died in 1450, in Toulon-sur-Allier, Allier, Auvergne, France, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1386–1450":"1386–1450","1381–1419":"1381–1419","1409–1450":"1409–1450","1410–Male":"1410–Surnud","1411–Male":"1411–Surnud","1412–Male":"1412–Surnud","1413–Male":"1413–Surnud","1415–Male":"1415–Surnud","abt. 1413":"umbes 1413","1450":"1450","1381":"1381","abt 1411":"umbes 1411","1415":"1415","1413":"1413","1412":"1412","1411":"1411","ABT. 1410":"umbes 1410","1410":"1410","1386":"1386","1409":"1409","ABT. 1412":"umbes 1412","1419":"1419","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Caldwell, Worcester, England":"Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Alston Hall, Worcester ENG":"Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Worcester, Worcestershire, England":"Worceste